In [41]:
mat = scio.loadmat('ex7faces.mat')
x = pd.DataFrame(mat['X'])

scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled = scaler.fit_transform(x)

def to_matrix(row, x, y):
    if hasattr(row, 'values'):
        return row.values.reshape(x, y, order='F')
    return row.reshape(x, y, order='F')
In [82]:
rows = 10
cols = 10
samples = x.sample(rows*cols)
scaled_samples = scaled[samples.index]

matrices = [to_matrix(row, 32, 32) for _, row in samples.iterrows()]

fig, subplots = plt.subplots(rows, cols, figsize=(12, 12), subplot_kw={'xticks': [], 'yticks':[]})
for row in range(rows):
    for col in range(cols):
        i = row * rows + col
        img = matrices[i]
        subplots[row][col].imshow(img)
        
plt.show()

from mpl_toolkits import mplot3d
%matplotlib widget
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


img = mpimg.imread('picture.png')

img_rgb = (img * 256).astype(int)

img = img.reshape(len(img), -1)
img_scaler = StandardScaler()
img_scaled = img_scaler.fit_transform(img)

proj3d, _, _ = main.pca(img_scaled, 3)
proj2d, _, _ = main.pca(img_scaled, 2)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(13, 5))
ax = fig.add_subplot(131)
ax.imshow(img_rgb)

ax = fig.add_subplot(132)
ax.scatter(proj2d[:, 0], proj2d[:, 1])

ax = fig.add_subplot(133, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(proj3d[:, 0], proj3d[:, 1], proj3d[:, 2])

plt.show()
